value.0: There is nothing noble in your manner. Get away from me, you evil, evil <man/woman>!
Vile monster. You'll get no gold from me. Ask your questions and leave.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> You... you wouldn't. There are guards all through the city... you would be seen...
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> You... you wouldn't... that vile, awful place? I'll have the plague by morn, and countless other filthy... conditions! I'll... I'll pay you to leave me alone right now!
You look quick with a weapon. The Shining Knight Arms and Armor in the City Core may have what you are looking for.
Ah, and if you wish to bolster yourself with a hireling, the Trade of Blades mercenary enclave in the City Core is where the adventurers are gathering.
Are scrolls and incantations your interest? You might wish to make yourself known at the Cloaktower in the Beggar's Nest.
You seem to move by Nature's hand? Perhaps the Druid Tree here in the Dock's district would be a location of interest for you.
I get the sense, however, that you seek something larcenous in nature. I'd suggest visiting the Moonstone Mask in the City Core.
Neverwinter has always been divided into separate Districts but, with the militia situated everywhere, it has become all the more apparent.
Which of the five is of interest to you? The Beggar's Nest, the Docks, the Blacklake district, the prison or the City Core?
I have little interest in the prison's affairs. There is already too much to worry about without fretting over the inmates or riots.
Now there are even rumors of prisoners trying to run free in the streets - You are better off leaving it alone.
Our more important institutions are located around Castle Never in the the center of Neverwinter's government.
<StartCheck>[Intimidate]</Start> Give me gold or I'll drag you through the Beggar's Nest.
